His office is right downstairs.

00:24:41.180 --> 00:24:43.180
Mr. Darling, what do you say?

00:24:43.180 --> 00:24:45.180
Well, you might get an idea from some of my work.

00:24:45.180 --> 00:24:47.180
Ideas? He's so modest.

00:24:47.180 --> 00:24:49.180
More like inspirations.

00:24:49.180 --> 00:24:51.180
Your work is incredible, Mr. Darling.

00:24:51.180 --> 00:24:53.180
We're thinking of calling it Four Winds.

00:24:53.180 --> 00:24:55.180
Four Winds?

00:24:55.180 --> 00:24:57.180
The home your father refuses to build for us.

00:24:57.180 --> 00:24:59.180
We're willing to give you a carte blanche.

00:24:59.180 --> 00:25:01.180
I'm not refusing. He's not refusing.

00:25:01.180 --> 00:25:03.180
No, it's just that, you know, we're about...

00:25:03.180 --> 00:25:05.180
Did you say carte blanche?

00:25:05.180 --> 00:25:07.180
I know, I know. You're all fun a journey, a quest.

00:25:07.180 --> 00:25:09.180
Have you ever seen tropical mosquitoes?

00:25:09.180 --> 00:25:11.180
Bigger than squirrels.

00:25:13.180 --> 00:25:15.180
Build us our dream house.

00:25:15.180 --> 00:25:17.180
We want to live in a darling.

00:25:17.180 --> 00:25:19.180
A darling.

00:25:19.180 --> 00:25:21.180
Darling?

00:25:21.180 --> 00:25:23.180
Oh, I always dreamed.

00:25:23.180 --> 00:25:25.180
No, I can't.

00:25:25.180 --> 00:25:27.180
I'm afraid our plans are ironclad.

00:25:27.180 --> 00:25:29.180
Hello, everyone.

00:25:29.180 --> 00:25:31.180
Hi, Mom.

00:25:31.180 --> 00:25:33.180
Hi, Janet. These are the Crepplehorns.

00:25:33.180 --> 00:25:35.180
We just love your home.

00:25:35.180 --> 00:25:37.180
It's got so much potential.

00:25:37.180 --> 00:25:39.180
Thank you.

00:25:39.180 --> 00:25:41.180
Of course, we'd rather your husband designed something for us.

00:25:41.180 --> 00:25:43.180
But he won't take our offer.

00:25:43.180 --> 00:25:45.180
An offer, Marshal?

00:25:45.180 --> 00:25:47.180
Well, that's nothing.

00:25:47.180 --> 00:25:49.180
Think it over, Mr. Darling.

00:25:49.180 --> 00:25:52.580
Bye.

00:25:52.580 --> 00:25:54.580
Have you thought it over yet, Dad?

00:25:54.580 --> 00:25:56.580
Well, there's nothing to think about, sport.

00:25:56.580 --> 00:25:58.580
Except, of course, our great adventure.

00:25:58.580 --> 00:26:00.580
A fantasy soon to become a reality.

00:26:02.580 --> 00:26:06.790
Mango Island?

00:26:06.790 --> 00:26:08.790
A fantasy soon to become a reality?

00:26:08.790 --> 00:26:19.400
Soon to become a nightmare.

00:26:19.400 --> 00:26:23.130
Times ticking away.

00:26:23.130 --> 00:26:25.130
Every day we're one step closer to adventure excitement.

00:26:25.130 --> 00:26:27.130
Huh?

00:26:27.130 --> 00:26:29.130
Oh, um, look what came today.

00:26:29.130 --> 00:26:31.130
Those? The tickets?

00:26:31.130 --> 00:26:33.130
Looks like they've been taking steroids.

00:26:33.130 --> 00:26:35.130
Well, it's, um...

00:26:35.130 --> 00:26:37.130
It's not very easy to get to Mango Island, sport.

00:26:37.130 --> 00:26:39.130
We have to change plane six times.

00:26:39.130 --> 00:26:41.130
Six times?

00:26:41.130 --> 00:26:43.130
Yeah. And then we have to take a ferry over from Fiji.

00:26:43.130 --> 00:26:45.130
And we're five days on the ferry.

00:26:45.130 --> 00:26:47.130
Five days?

00:26:47.130 --> 00:26:49.130
Yeah, and of course the Almanac says

00:26:49.130 --> 00:26:51.130
that this really is not the best time to go to Mango Island.

00:26:51.130 --> 00:26:53.130
Monsoon season.

00:26:53.130 --> 00:26:55.130
Monsoon season.

00:26:55.130 --> 00:26:57.130
And then there's Mount Nambi Kaivu.

00:26:57.130 --> 00:26:59.130
Tell me there's a beautiful view.

00:26:59.130 --> 00:27:03.130
No. It's a smoldering, erratic, and very active volcano.

00:27:03.130 --> 00:27:05.130
Oh. That does it, Marshall.

00:27:05.130 --> 00:27:07.130
I have played along with the mango mashing.

00:27:07.130 --> 00:27:09.130
I have put up with the conch shell wake-up calls,

00:27:09.130 --> 00:27:11.130
