Slime Time is sponsored by McDonald's,

01:30:16.320 --> 01:30:19.320
Sega, and the place where only kids win Nickelodeon.

01:30:20.320 --> 01:30:22.320
AXE Murder with Blood,

01:30:22.320 --> 01:30:58.820
dripping from our grizzly weapon.

01:30:59.820 --> 01:31:02.820
Or Mummy Wrapped in Wrotten Bedgages.

01:31:02.820 --> 01:31:04.820
What about a razor sharp hook

01:31:04.820 --> 01:31:06.820
where her hand should be?

01:31:06.820 --> 01:31:08.820
No, no...

01:31:08.820 --> 01:31:10.820
A zombie with sunken eyes

01:31:10.820 --> 01:31:12.820
and all stiff-like.

01:31:12.820 --> 01:31:14.820
It sounds like Kristen's up tonight.

01:31:14.820 --> 01:31:17.820
We're trying to guess what axe she's going to pull to Scareva.

01:31:18.820 --> 01:31:20.820
I liked it when she dressed up as the prom queen.

01:31:20.820 --> 01:31:22.820
Yeah, whatever it is.

01:31:22.820 --> 01:31:25.820
Whatever it is, I hope she gets here soon.

01:31:25.820 --> 01:31:35.940
Cool.

01:31:35.940 --> 01:31:37.940
Hey, where'd you get that stuff?

01:31:37.940 --> 01:31:38.940
Up in the attic.

01:31:38.940 --> 01:31:43.940
I, uh, think my parents were old hippies or something.

01:31:43.940 --> 01:31:48.900
Here.

01:31:48.900 --> 01:31:50.900
Groovy, man.

01:31:50.900 --> 01:31:51.900
And here.

01:31:51.900 --> 01:31:55.900
Whoa, Sakatumi.

01:31:55.900 --> 01:31:57.900
What's this got to do with your store?

01:31:57.900 --> 01:32:00.900
There's an old saying that goes,

01:32:00.900 --> 01:32:02.900
you don't learn from the past,

01:32:02.900 --> 01:32:05.900
you'll be doomed to repeat it.

01:32:05.900 --> 01:32:12.620
My story's a little different.

01:32:12.620 --> 01:32:15.620
In my tale, if you don't learn from the present,

01:32:15.620 --> 01:32:17.620
you'll repeat the past.

01:32:17.620 --> 01:32:21.270
You're doomed.

01:32:21.270 --> 01:32:33.180
Admitted for the approval of the Midnight Society,

01:32:33.180 --> 01:32:39.020
I call this story,

01:32:39.020 --> 01:32:42.020
the tale of Locker 22.

01:32:42.020 --> 01:32:56.590
We haven't put anyone out here for years,

01:32:56.590 --> 01:32:58.590
but we're busting at the seams.

01:32:58.590 --> 01:33:00.590
I don't know where all these kids come from.

01:33:00.590 --> 01:33:04.450
Locker 22.

01:33:04.450 --> 01:33:06.450
Home sweet home.

01:33:06.450 --> 01:33:14.360
Um, it's kind of far from things.

01:33:14.360 --> 01:33:16.360
Are you complaining?

01:33:16.360 --> 01:33:17.360
No.

01:33:17.360 --> 01:33:20.360
Look, I've been here far too long to take grief from a transfer.

01:33:20.360 --> 01:33:22.360
It's only been here five minutes.

01:33:22.360 --> 01:33:23.360
I'm sorry.

01:33:23.360 --> 01:33:25.360
This will be fine.

01:33:25.360 --> 01:33:27.360
Good.

01:33:27.360 --> 01:33:48.260
Welcome to Derby, Miss Dufault.

01:33:48.260 --> 01:33:58.180
Carefully suck the liquid into the pipette like so,

01:33:58.180 --> 01:34:05.380
and hold your finger on the end so that it doesn't run out.

01:34:05.380 --> 01:34:17.620
Simple.

01:34:17.620 --> 01:34:19.620
We'll pick it up tomorrow.

01:34:19.620 --> 01:34:28.540
Next time, we do it with acid.

01:34:28.540 --> 01:34:31.540
Mmm, tasty.

01:34:31.540 --> 01:34:36.950
Keep moving, bozos.

01:34:36.950 --> 01:34:38.950
Hey, you okay?

01:34:38.950 --> 01:34:42.640
Yes.

01:34:42.640 --> 01:34:43.640
I'm Chris.

01:34:43.640 --> 01:34:45.640
You new here?

01:34:45.640 --> 01:34:46.640
Yeah.

01:34:46.640 --> 01:34:48.640
It's no biggie.

01:34:48.640 --> 01:34:50.640
What's your name?

01:34:50.640 --> 01:34:51.640
Ginny.

01:34:51.640 --> 01:34:54.640
I never woke with things like this at my old school.

01:34:54.640 --> 01:34:56.640
Oh, where are you from?

01:34:56.640 --> 01:34:58.640
Paris.

01:34:58.640 --> 01:35:00.640
My parents came here for business.

01:35:00.640 --> 01:35:01.640
Oh.

01:35:01.640 --> 01:35:02.640
Well, don't sweat it.

01:35:02.640 --> 01:35:04.640
You'll pick it up.

01:35:04.640 --> 01:35:06.640
You lost it?

01:35:06.640 --> 01:35:07.640
Everybody does it first.

01:35:07.640 --> 01:35:09.640
This place is huge.

01:35:09.640 --> 01:35:11.640
Hey, what's your next class?

01:35:11.640 --> 01:35:13.640
Um, all right.

01:35:13.640 --> 01:35:16.640
You know how to get there?

01:35:16.640 --> 01:35:18.640
Come on, I'll show you.

01:35:18.640 --> 01:35:19.640
Thanks.

01:35:19.640 --> 01:35:25.100
You scared me.

01:35:25.100 --> 01:35:31.960
I thought everybody left.

01:35:31.960 --> 01:35:32.960
I'm coming.

01:35:32.960 --> 01:36:02.380
What do you, uh,

01:36:02.380 --> 01:36:04.380
what do you think of the new girl?

01:36:04.380 --> 01:36:05.380
I don't know.

01:36:05.380 --> 01:36:07.380
Kind of weird, Fritz.

01:36:07.380 --> 01:36:09.380
See what happened, chemistry?

01:36:09.380 --> 01:36:11.380
No, no, what?

01:36:11.380 --> 01:36:15.380
Well, she had this straw thing,

01:36:15.380 --> 01:36:17.380
and she sucked up the water.

01:36:17.380 --> 01:36:19.380
Yeah.

01:36:19.380 --> 01:36:20.380
Then what?

01:36:20.380 --> 01:36:24.380
Well, then she sort of did this.

01:36:26.380 --> 01:36:54.570
Did I say something about giving me grief, Mr. Faux?

01:36:54.570 --> 01:36:55.570
But, sir, I didn't.

01:36:55.570 --> 01:36:57.570
If you're a troublemaker,

01:36:57.570 --> 01:36:59.570
you've crossed paths with the wrong man.

01:36:59.570 --> 01:37:35.130
What do you want?

01:37:35.130 --> 01:37:53.630
Go.

01:37:53.630 --> 01:37:54.630
Listen, I heard about what happened

01:37:54.630 --> 01:37:55.630
with those guys at lunch to get them.

01:37:55.630 --> 01:37:57.630
Come on, just start it.

01:37:57.630 --> 01:38:01.630
Burn out now, you're not gonna make it.

01:38:01.630 --> 01:38:02.630
Hey, you okay?

01:38:02.630 --> 01:38:05.630
I, uh...

01:38:05.630 --> 01:38:07.630
I saw something.

01:38:07.630 --> 01:38:08.630
What?

01:38:08.630 --> 01:38:10.630
Um...

01:38:10.630 --> 01:38:12.630
I saw a...

01:38:12.630 --> 01:38:14.630
You saw a?

01:38:14.630 --> 01:38:15.630
I'll forget.

01:38:15.630 --> 01:38:17.630
Come on, Julie, what'd you see?

01:38:17.630 --> 01:38:18.630
You promised not to laugh.

01:38:18.630 --> 01:38:21.630
I crossed my heart.

01:38:21.630 --> 01:38:24.630
Look, I know this sounds crazy.

01:38:24.630 --> 01:38:27.630
I think I saw a ghost.

01:38:27.630 --> 01:38:28.630
A ghost?

01:38:28.630 --> 01:38:30.630
Forget I said anything.

01:38:30.630 --> 01:38:31.630
Julie.

01:38:31.630 --> 01:39:00.090
Hello?

01:39:00.090 --> 01:39:18.220
What's the matter?

01:39:18.220 --> 01:39:20.220
I trusted you and you had to tell everybody

01:39:20.220 --> 01:39:21.220
what I told you.

01:39:21.220 --> 01:39:22.220
Julie, I didn't.

01:39:22.220 --> 01:39:24.220
You're worse than those jerks in the cafeteria

01:39:24.220 --> 01:39:26.220
because you pretend to be nice.

01:39:26.220 --> 01:39:27.220
Wait a minute, wait.

01:39:27.220 --> 01:39:28.220
I should have seen you coming.

01:39:28.220 --> 01:39:29.220
Wait.

01:39:29.220 --> 01:39:34.310
I only told one person.

01:39:34.310 --> 01:39:36.310
I didn't know they were gonna make it news.

01:39:36.310 --> 01:39:37.310
Well, they did.

01:39:37.310 --> 01:39:39.310
Now, everybody thinks I'm the crazy new foreign kid.

01:39:39.310 --> 01:39:41.310
Listen, I did it for a reason, okay?

01:39:41.310 --> 01:39:42.310
I'm sure.

01:39:42.310 --> 01:39:58.140
Hope you all got a good laugh.

01:39:58.140 --> 01:39:59.140
I'm sorry.

01:39:59.140 --> 01:40:01.640
I didn't mean to scare you.

01:40:01.640 --> 01:40:04.640
Although, I didn't think anything could scare you.

01:40:04.640 --> 01:40:06.640
As long as you're a ghost, boss.

01:40:06.640 --> 01:40:07.640
Stop it.

01:40:07.640 --> 01:40:13.310
Whoa.

01:40:21.950 --> 01:41:13.650
What did you call me?

01:41:13.650 --> 01:41:14.650
I'm sorry.

01:41:14.650 --> 01:41:15.650
Moon Dance.

01:41:15.650 --> 01:41:18.650
This necklace is like boss.

01:41:18.650 --> 01:41:21.820
Whoa.

01:41:21.820 --> 01:41:22.820
Be cool.

01:41:22.820 --> 01:41:45.660
I'm waiting, Miss Warren.

01:41:45.660 --> 01:42:15.820
They're not squishy and sweet

01:42:15.820 --> 01:42:17.820
and they don't make you go googaloo.

01:42:17.820 --> 01:42:18.820
They're the Nicktoons

01:42:18.820 --> 01:42:20.820
and they're not here to be cuddling.

01:42:20.820 --> 01:42:22.820
Dug, Ren and Stimpy, the Rugrats.

01:42:22.820 --> 01:42:24.820
They'll battle the biggest bully.

01:42:24.820 --> 01:42:26.820
Climb the highest toilet even.

01:42:26.820 --> 01:42:28.820
Well, you don't wanna know.

01:42:28.820 --> 01:42:29.820
These are no stuffed animals.

01:42:29.820 --> 01:42:30.820
They've got wheel problems,

01:42:30.820 --> 01:42:31.820
wheel adventures,

01:42:31.820 --> 01:42:32.820
and they're real loud.

01:42:32.820 --> 01:42:34.820
Winnie's the wickedest.

01:42:34.820 --> 01:42:35.820
Hello.

01:42:35.820 --> 01:42:36.820
Sarah's the sexiest.

01:42:36.820 --> 01:42:38.820
Would thou dance with me?

01:42:38.820 --> 01:42:40.820
And Mary's the hungriest.

01:42:40.820 --> 01:42:42.820
No time for singing.

01:42:42.820 --> 01:42:44.820
They're here to have some fun

01:42:44.820 --> 01:42:46.820
and practice a little witchcraft

01:42:46.820 --> 01:42:48.820
if they could only get it right.

01:42:48.820 --> 01:42:49.820
She did it.

01:42:49.820 --> 01:42:54.820
Hocus Pocus, rated PG, starts Friday, July 16th.

01:42:54.820 --> 01:42:56.820
I love the taste of milk, Max.

01:42:56.820 --> 01:42:58.820
It's a great taste.

01:42:58.820 --> 01:43:01.820
Which is why, for the pleasure of a tall, tasty glass,

01:43:01.820 --> 01:43:03.820
I do almost anything.

01:43:03.820 --> 01:43:06.820
For the smooth, cool goodness of milk,

01:43:06.820 --> 01:43:08.820
I fly to the farthest galaxy.

01:43:08.820 --> 01:43:10.820
For the cold, refreshing taste of milk,

01:43:10.820 --> 01:43:12.820
I crawl through the burning wasteland.

01:43:12.820 --> 01:43:15.820
For one, satisfying, yummy gulp of milk,

01:43:15.820 --> 01:43:17.820
I'd stretch myself to the limits.

01:43:17.820 --> 01:43:19.820
I do homework, Max.

01:43:19.820 --> 01:43:20.820
Wow.

01:43:20.820 --> 01:43:21.820
Milk.

01:43:21.820 --> 01:43:23.820
It tastes so good.

01:43:23.820 --> 01:43:26.820
You know, when you're shopping for cereal,

01:43:26.820 --> 01:43:28.820
I suggest you walk this way

01:43:28.820 --> 01:43:31.820
because it keeps the expensive cereals out of reach

01:43:31.820 --> 01:43:33.820
and puts you in a better position

01:43:33.820 --> 01:43:34.820
to find malto meal cereals.

01:43:34.820 --> 01:43:36.820
See, they're usually down here.

01:43:36.820 --> 01:43:38.820
Well, in a bag.

01:43:38.820 --> 01:43:40.820
And they're every bit as good as these

01:43:40.820 --> 01:43:41.820
and cost less.

01:43:41.820 --> 01:43:42.820
See?

01:43:42.820 --> 01:43:44.820
This one costs about a dollar less.

01:43:44.820 --> 01:43:46.820
A dollar?

01:43:46.820 --> 01:43:47.820
Malto meal.

01:43:47.820 --> 01:43:49.820
The savings are in the bag.

01:43:49.820 --> 01:43:55.980
You really ought to come down here.

01:43:59.980 --> 01:44:24.120
We have to talk.

01:44:24.120 --> 01:44:26.120
Look, I'm sorry about what happened.

01:44:26.120 --> 01:44:27.120
That's all I can say.

01:44:27.120 --> 01:44:30.120
You said you told someone about what I saw for one reason.

01:44:30.120 --> 01:44:31.120
What was it?

01:44:31.120 --> 01:44:35.290
What?

01:44:35.290 --> 01:44:38.290
Look, there's been stuff going around

01:44:38.290 --> 01:44:41.290
about a ghost haunting this place for years.

01:44:41.290 --> 01:44:44.290
I know somebody who knows somebody who said they saw it.

01:44:44.290 --> 01:44:45.290
That's all.

01:44:45.290 --> 01:44:47.290
I didn't mean to embarrass you.

01:44:47.290 --> 01:44:48.290
Wait.

01:44:48.290 --> 01:44:52.460
I want to show you something.

01:44:52.460 --> 01:44:53.460
Look, I gotta go.

01:44:53.460 --> 01:44:54.460
Please?

01:44:54.460 --> 01:45:08.620
You owe me.

01:45:08.620 --> 01:45:10.620
Look, whoever had my locker before

01:45:10.620 --> 01:45:12.620
put a flower sticker there.

01:45:12.620 --> 01:45:13.620
See that?

01:45:13.620 --> 01:45:14.620
Uh, yeah.

01:45:14.620 --> 01:45:15.620
This necklace.

01:45:15.620 --> 01:45:17.620
I found it in my locker.

01:45:17.620 --> 01:45:19.620
It must have belonged to the same person.

01:45:19.620 --> 01:45:20.620
Yes, sir.

01:45:20.620 --> 01:45:22.620
Look around.

01:45:22.620 --> 01:45:23.620
The paint is old.

01:45:23.620 --> 01:45:25.620
Like nothing has been done for years.

01:45:25.620 --> 01:45:26.620
Right?

01:45:26.620 --> 01:45:29.620
Look, I'm sorry about those guys giving you a hard time.

01:45:29.620 --> 01:45:31.620
But you're getting a little spooky on me, all right?

01:45:31.620 --> 01:45:32.620
Spooky?

01:45:32.620 --> 01:45:35.620
You haven't seen anything yet.

01:45:35.620 --> 01:45:41.530
What happened?

01:45:41.530 --> 01:45:42.530
How'd you do that?

01:45:42.530 --> 01:45:43.530
I don't know.

01:45:43.530 --> 01:45:46.530
It happened to me before when I put on this necklace.

01:45:46.530 --> 01:45:48.530
It's like I jumped back in time.

01:45:48.530 --> 01:45:49.530
Candy.

01:45:49.530 --> 01:45:53.220
Who's this?

01:45:53.220 --> 01:45:56.220
Uh, you don't know him?

01:45:56.220 --> 01:45:58.220
No.

01:45:58.220 --> 01:46:00.220
Are you new?

01:46:02.220 --> 01:46:03.220
I don't know.

01:46:03.220 --> 01:46:06.220
You don't know?

01:46:06.220 --> 01:46:08.220
If he figures it out,

01:46:08.220 --> 01:46:10.220
invite him over tonight.

01:46:10.220 --> 01:46:12.220
I got the Beatles' white album.

01:46:12.220 --> 01:46:14.220
Bye.

01:46:14.220 --> 01:46:18.220
Beatles' white album?

01:46:18.220 --> 01:46:20.220
Look at this.

01:46:20.220 --> 01:46:21.220
See?

01:46:21.220 --> 01:46:22.220
This is my locker.

01:46:22.220 --> 01:46:24.220
This is the flower.

01:46:24.220 --> 01:46:25.220
Candy?

01:46:25.220 --> 01:46:27.220
That girl called you candy.

01:46:27.220 --> 01:46:29.220
Miss Laura.

01:46:29.220 --> 01:46:30.220
Shaffner?

01:46:30.220 --> 01:46:33.220
Mr. Shaffner.

01:46:33.220 --> 01:46:35.220
Who are you?

01:46:35.220 --> 01:46:38.220
Um, I'm new.

01:46:38.220 --> 01:46:43.430
Learn some manners.

01:46:43.430 --> 01:46:45.430
No, Miss Warren.

01:46:45.430 --> 01:46:47.430
Not tomorrow, not next week.

01:46:47.430 --> 01:46:48.430
Now!

01:46:48.430 --> 01:46:51.430
No buts.

01:46:51.430 --> 01:46:53.430
I'll stay late today to help.

01:46:53.430 --> 01:46:56.430
But if your chemistry project isn't done by four o'clock,

01:46:56.430 --> 01:46:59.430
you'll be staring at a big fat F

01:46:59.430 --> 01:47:01.430
in summer school.

01:47:01.430 --> 01:47:02.430
You did?

01:47:02.430 --> 01:47:06.190
Groovy.

01:47:06.190 --> 01:47:10.690
I'll meet you in the lab.

01:47:10.690 --> 01:47:12.690
Something strange happened, Chris.

01:47:12.690 --> 01:47:14.690
Yeah, tell me about it.

01:47:14.690 --> 01:47:16.690
That was Shaffner.

01:47:16.690 --> 01:47:18.690
He was, he was young.

01:47:18.690 --> 01:47:20.690
I know.

01:47:20.690 --> 01:47:22.690
It's like if we're back in the 60s.

01:47:22.690 --> 01:47:24.690
How could that happen?

01:47:24.690 --> 01:47:26.690
You said it was your necklace.

01:47:26.690 --> 01:47:27.690
Take it off.

01:47:27.690 --> 01:47:34.550
Oh, man.

01:47:34.550 --> 01:47:36.550
Oh, man, this is wild.

01:47:36.550 --> 01:47:38.550
It is the necklace.

01:47:38.550 --> 01:47:41.550
It has some kind of power.

01:47:41.550 --> 01:47:43.550
Candy?

01:47:43.550 --> 01:47:45.550
That girl called you candy.

01:47:45.550 --> 01:47:47.550
Who is candy?

01:47:47.550 --> 01:47:49.550
I don't know, but we can find out.

01:47:49.550 --> 01:47:51.550
Come on.

01:47:51.550 --> 01:48:01.100
Hey, hey.

01:48:01.100 --> 01:48:03.100
You see, I'm checking 1968.

01:48:03.100 --> 01:48:06.800
You know when the white album came out?

01:48:06.800 --> 01:48:07.800
Bingo.

01:48:07.800 --> 01:48:08.800
What?

01:48:08.800 --> 01:48:10.800
Candy Warren, locker 22.

01:48:10.800 --> 01:48:12.800
Yeah, that was a locker, all right.

01:48:12.800 --> 01:48:16.720
Who is she?

01:48:16.720 --> 01:48:18.720
I don't get it. Why isn't she here?

01:48:18.720 --> 01:48:20.720
I checked three times. She isn't here.

01:48:20.720 --> 01:48:24.030
There.

01:48:24.030 --> 01:48:26.030
That's her.

01:48:26.030 --> 01:48:28.030
That's the ghost.

01:48:28.030 --> 01:48:33.460
This is real, isn't it?

01:48:33.460 --> 01:48:36.460
I guess. We can't both be crazy.

01:48:36.460 --> 01:48:39.460
Why is Candy showing yourself to me?

01:48:39.460 --> 01:48:41.460
And why do they think I'm Candy?

01:48:41.460 --> 01:48:43.460
I don't know.

01:48:43.460 --> 01:48:45.460
Listen, whatever's going on here,

01:48:45.460 --> 01:48:47.460
we can't handle it, all right?

01:48:47.460 --> 01:48:49.460
What do we do?

01:48:49.460 --> 01:48:51.460
I don't know.

01:48:51.460 --> 01:48:53.460
I feel like she's trying to tell me something, Chris.

01:48:53.460 --> 01:48:55.460
This is happening for a reason.

01:48:55.460 --> 01:48:57.460
Maybe. Ah, come on. Let's get out of here.

01:48:57.460 --> 01:48:59.460
I have to get my books.

01:48:59.460 --> 01:49:01.460
Let's talk tonight.

01:49:01.460 --> 01:49:02.460
Okay, later.

01:49:02.460 --> 01:49:20.010
Mr. Ratto.

01:49:20.010 --> 01:49:22.010
Chris, you're here late.

01:49:22.010 --> 01:49:25.010
Mr. Ratto, you've been teaching here, like, forever, right?

01:49:25.010 --> 01:49:28.010
Yeah, I suppose 30 years is forever to you.

01:49:28.010 --> 01:49:30.010
Did you know Candy Warren?

01:49:30.010 --> 01:49:33.010
Candy Warren.

01:49:33.010 --> 01:49:36.010
Haven't thought of her in years.

01:49:36.010 --> 01:49:38.010
I'm sure I knew her.

01:49:38.010 --> 01:49:40.010
Sweet girl.

01:49:40.010 --> 01:49:42.010
It's such a tragedy.

01:49:42.010 --> 01:49:44.010
Well, how did she die? Was she, like, sick or something?

01:49:44.010 --> 01:49:46.010
Oh, heavens, no.

01:49:46.010 --> 01:49:48.010
It was a horrible accident.

01:49:48.010 --> 01:49:50.010
What, a car crash?

01:49:50.010 --> 01:49:52.010
No, it happened right here.

01:49:52.010 --> 01:50:03.260
Derby?

01:50:03.260 --> 01:50:10.380
Ms. Warren, now!

01:50:10.380 --> 01:50:12.380
She was staying late after school on some

01:50:12.380 --> 01:50:14.380
chemistry project or something.

01:50:14.380 --> 01:50:17.380
Apparently, she got a little careless.

01:50:17.380 --> 01:50:20.380
And there was, you know,

01:50:20.380 --> 01:50:26.540
explosion and fire and

01:50:26.540 --> 01:50:30.880
hard to even think about it now.

01:50:30.880 --> 01:50:32.880
Why do you ask?

01:50:32.880 --> 01:50:34.880
Who was the teacher?

01:50:34.880 --> 01:50:37.880
Oh, well, many years ago, I...

01:50:37.880 --> 01:50:41.450
I don't know.

01:50:41.450 --> 01:50:43.450
Thanks, Mr. Ratto.

01:50:43.450 --> 01:50:45.450
Oh, it was Mr. Schaffner.

01:50:45.450 --> 01:50:47.450
Before he became the assistant principal,

01:50:47.450 --> 01:50:50.450
he worked in the chemistry department.

01:50:50.450 --> 01:51:00.740
Nice of you to join me.

01:51:00.740 --> 01:51:29.580
Sit.

01:51:29.580 --> 01:51:32.580
Worksheets, thermometer, beakers,

01:51:32.580 --> 01:51:38.020
and a pipette for measuring.

01:51:38.020 --> 01:51:51.030
Well, explain what we're doing.

01:51:51.030 --> 01:51:53.030
We're identifying compounds

01:51:53.030 --> 01:51:55.030
by determining their melting points.

01:51:55.030 --> 01:51:59.030
Or would you like to skip right to summer school now?

01:51:59.030 --> 01:52:02.470
No, no, I want to try.

01:52:02.470 --> 01:52:04.470
How do I do this?

01:52:04.470 --> 01:52:09.010
That's what this test is about now, isn't it?

01:52:09.010 --> 01:52:11.010
I'll give you a little hint.

01:52:11.010 --> 01:52:14.010
Turn on the gas and light the burner.

01:52:14.010 --> 01:52:16.010
After that, you're on your own.

01:52:16.010 --> 01:52:40.820
I'll be back in 20 minutes.

01:52:40.820 --> 01:52:45.060
Candy, is Julie in the past?

01:52:45.060 --> 01:53:06.140
Listen, Candy, she's gonna die.

01:53:06.140 --> 01:54:13.670
You gotta stop her.

01:54:13.670 --> 01:54:16.670
Hey, don't you check your equipment, Mr. Schaffner?

01:54:16.670 --> 01:54:23.440
You could have been killed.

01:54:23.440 --> 01:54:25.440
I don't know what to say.

01:54:25.440 --> 01:54:29.680
Say you're in the wrong line of work.

01:54:29.680 --> 01:54:31.680
Thank God you saw this.

01:54:31.680 --> 01:54:38.320
If you hadn't...

01:54:38.320 --> 01:54:40.320
I would have been toast.

01:54:40.320 --> 01:54:43.320
Yeah, I saw her. She brought me back.

01:54:51.560 --> 01:54:54.560
Can I ask what you're doing here so late?

01:54:54.560 --> 01:54:57.560
I was helping her with the locker.

01:54:57.560 --> 01:55:01.420
It stuck.

01:55:01.420 --> 01:55:03.420
At least it was stuck.

01:55:03.420 --> 01:55:05.420
Oh, I know it used to stick for me all the time, too.

01:55:05.420 --> 01:55:07.420
For you?

01:55:07.420 --> 01:55:09.420
That was your locker?

01:55:09.420 --> 01:55:11.420
Oh, back in the dark ages.

01:55:11.420 --> 01:55:14.420
You must be Julie Defoe.

01:55:14.420 --> 01:55:16.420
Nice to meet you.

01:55:16.420 --> 01:55:18.420
I'm the assistant principal, Ms. Warren.

01:55:18.420 --> 01:55:28.190
Candy Warren.

01:55:28.190 --> 01:55:36.340
My office, please.

01:55:36.340 --> 01:55:38.340
The end.

01:55:38.340 --> 01:55:39.340
Far out.

01:55:39.340 --> 01:55:40.340
Oh, solid.

01:55:40.340 --> 01:55:42.340
Psychedelic.

01:55:42.340 --> 01:55:44.340
Um...

01:55:44.340 --> 01:55:49.820
Nito?

01:55:49.820 --> 01:55:51.820
I'll give you my bag.

01:55:51.820 --> 01:55:53.820
Sorry.

01:55:53.820 --> 01:55:55.820
Thanks, man.

01:55:55.820 --> 01:55:57.820
Good story for you.

